'''Adam Bielański''' (14 December 1912 – 4 September 2016)<ref>{{cite web|title=W wieku 104 lat zmarł prof. Adam Bielański |url=http://wiadomosci.wp.pl/kat,1342,title,W-wieku-104-lat-zmarl-prof-Adam-Bielanski,wid,18495563,wiadomosc.html?ticaid=117aef |language=pl |date=6 September 2016 |accessdate=6 September 2016}}</ref> was a Polish chemist and professor of [[Jagiellonian University]].<ref>{{Cite book|last=Bielański|first=Adam|title=Chemia ogólna i nieorganiczna|year=1981|publisher=[[Państwowe Wydawnictwo Naukowe]]|place=Warsaw|isbn=83-01-02626-X}}</ref> He was a member of the [[Polish Academy of Science]]. He was the author of several university-level books on [[inorganic chemistry]], many of which are standard textbooks for students at most universities in Poland.{{cn|date=September 2016}}

Bielański was born in [[Kraków]], at the time [[Grand Duchy of Cracow|part of]] [[Austria-Hungary]]. His brother Władysław (1911–1982) was a professor of [[biology]], as was his sister, Zofia Bielańska-Osuchowska. He [[centenarian|turned 100 years old]] in December 2012<ref name="Centenary">{{cite news|last=Warszawski|first=Marcin|title=Nigdy nie pracowałem nad eliksirem młodości|newspaper=[[Dziennik Polski]]|language=Polish|publisher=Wydawnictwo Jagiellonia SA|date=11 January 2013|url=http://www.dziennikpolski24.pl/pl/region/miasto-krakow/1256768-nigdy-nie-pracowalem-nad-eliksirem-mlodosci-zdjecia.html|accessdate=30 January 2013}}</ref> and died in 2016 at the age of 103.<ref>http://www.agh.edu.pl/info/article/odszedl-prof-adam-bielanski/</ref>

