==Distribution==
===International===
''Fringe'' premiered in Canada on [[CTV Television Network|CTV]] simultaneous to its U.S. premiere and was the most watched program in Canada that week.<ref>{{cite press release |url=http://www.bbm.ca/_documents/top_30_tv_programs_english/nat09082008.pdf |title=Top Programs – Total Canada (English) September 8–14, 2008 |publisher=[[BBM Canada]] |date=2008-09-19 |accessdate=2011-05-25 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110706165054/http://www.bbm.ca/_documents/top_30_tv_programs_english/nat09082008.pdf |archivedate=2011-07-06 |df=}}</ref> The show would fluctuate between airing on CTV and [[A (TV system)|A]] during its first two seasons. Beginning with the third season, ''Fringe'' was broadcast on [[Citytv|City]] in Canada.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://playbackonline.ca/2010/08/11/citytv-unveils-fall-premiere-dates/ |title=Citytv unveils fall premiere dates |last=Bailey |first=Katie |work=[[Playback (website)|Playback]] |date=2010-08-11 |accessdate=2011-05-25}}</ref>

A version of the show (edited for time) premiered on the [[Nine Network]] in Australia on September 17, 2008. In the season one episode "[[In Which We Meet Mr. Jones]]", the opening scene where doctors discover a parasite on Detective Loeb's heart was cut, going straight to the opening credits.<ref>{{cite press release |title=Fringe - Series Premiere - Wednesday, September 17 AT 8:30PM on Nine |url=http://www.ebroadcast.com.au/enews/nine/FRINGE---SERIES-PREMIERE---WEDNESDAY-SEPTEMBER-17-AT-8-30PM-ON-NINE-040908.html |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20090221090030/http://www.ebroadcast.com.au/enews/nine/FRINGE---SERIES-PREMIERE---WEDNESDAY-SEPTEMBER-17-AT-8-30PM-ON-NINE-040908.html |archivedate=2009-02-21 |publisher=[[Nine Network]] |date=2008-09-04 |accessdate=2008-09-16}}</ref>  Nine Network later dropped the show from its primetime schedule.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.tvtonight.com.au/2008/10/gone-fringe.html |title=Gone: ''Fringe'' |author=Knox, David |date=2008-10-17 |publisher=TV Tonight |accessdate=2008-12-13}}</ref> This was temporary as the show returned during the December to January non-ratings period.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.tvtonight.com.au/2008/12/nine-switches-fringe-episodes.html |title=Nine switches Fringe episodes |author=Knox, David |date=2008-12-03 |publisher=TV Tonight |accessdate=2011-05-22}}</ref> The series later moved to Nine's digital multi-channel, [[GO! (Australian TV channel)|GO!]], where the last few seasons were played out.

The series premiered in the United Kingdom on [[Sky1]] on October 5, 2008.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://sky1.sky.com/fringe-whats-it-all-about |title=Fringe: What's it All About? |date=2008-12-03 |publisher=Sky1 |accessdate=2012-05-03}}</ref>

=== Syndication ===
With 13 episodes in its final season, ''Fringe'' has a total of 100 episodes, a critical number for syndication deals for Warner Bros., and considered part of the reason for the show's final renewal. The show premiered in syndication on the [[Science (TV channel)|Science Network]] on November 20, 2012.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.deadline.com/2012/05/fringe-sells-in-off-network-syndication-to-science-channel/ |title='Fringe' Sells In Off-Network Syndication To Science Channel |date=2012-05-23 |accessdate=2012-06-20 |first=Nellie |last=Andreeva |website=[[Deadline Hollywood]]}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://insidetv.ew.com/2012/11/12/fringe-science-channel/ |title='Fringe': Science Channel to re-air all five seasons |date=2012-11-12 |accessdate=2013-01-18 |first=Hillary |last=Busis |publisher=[[Entertainment Weekly]]}}</ref>

=== Home video releases ===
The first season of ''Fringe'' was released on DVD and [[Blu-ray Disc]] on September 8, 2009 in region 1.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.amazon.com/dp/B001C4CI8U/ |title=Fringe: The Complete First Season (2008) |publisher=Amazon.com |accessdate=2012-05-08}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.tvshowsondvd.com/news/Fringe-Season-1-Press-Release/11983 |title=Fringe - Warner's Official Press Release Reveals Street Date for Season 1 Blu-ray & DVD |publisher=TVShowsOnDVD |date=2009-05-28 |accessdate=2011-04-30 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110825082743/http://www.tvshowsondvd.com/news/Fringe-Season-1-Press-Release/11983 |archivedate=2011-08-25 |df=}}</ref> In addition to all the episodes that had been aired, extras include three commentary tracks, unaired scenes, gag reels and behind the scenes features. A "''Fringe'' Pattern Analysis" feature is included on the Blu-ray version as an exclusive. The sets were released on September 28, 2009 in region 2<ref>{{cite web |url=http://film.thedigitalfix.com/content/id/71144/fringe-season-1-r2uk-bd-in-september-artwork-added.html |title=Fringe Season 1 (R2/UK BD) in September - Artwork added |publisher=Home Cinema |date=2009-07-24 |accessdate=2011-04-30}}</ref> and on September 30, 2009 in region 4.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.ezydvd.com.au/DVD/fringe-the-complete-1st-season-7-disc-box-set/dp/808305 |title=Fringe - The Complete 1st Season (7 Disc Box Set) |publisher=EzyDVD |accessdate=2012-05-08 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130708204732/http://www.ezydvd.com.au/DVD/fringe-the-complete-1st-season-7-disc-box-set/dp/808305 |archivedate=2013-07-08 |df=}}</ref>

The second season features four commentary tracks, a gag reel, deleted scenes, behind the scenes videos, and the episode "[[Unearthed (Fringe)|Unearthed]]", an episode, produced for the first season, which aired out of schedule during the second season. It was released on DVD and Blu-ray on September 14, 2010 in region 1,<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.amazon.com/dp/B002JVWRD6/ |title=Fringe: The Complete Second Season (2009) |publisher=Amazon.com |accessdate=2012-05-08}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.tvshowsondvd.com/news/Fringe-Season-2/13922 |title=Fringe - The Complete 2nd Season Now Officially Announced on DVD and Blu-ray |publisher=TVShowsOnDVD |date=2010-06-16 |accessdate=2011-05-15 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20111017180800/http://www.tvshowsondvd.com/news/Fringe-Season-2/13922 |archivedate=2011-10-17 |df=}}</ref> on September 27, 2010 in region 2,<ref>{{cite web |url=http://film.thedigitalfix.com/content/id/72844/fringe-and-supernatural-uk-in-september.html |title=Fringe & Supernatural (UK) in September |publisher=Home Cinema |date=2010-07-22 |accessdate=2011-05-15}}</ref> and on November 10, 2010 in region 4.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.ezydvd.com.au/blu-ray/fringe-the-complete-2nd-season-4-disc-set-blu-ray/dp/813845 |title=Fringe - The Complete 2nd Season (4 Disc Set) (Blu-ray) |publisher=EzyDVD |accessdate=2012-05-08 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130708204616/http://www.ezydvd.com.au/blu-ray/fringe-the-complete-2nd-season-4-disc-set-blu-ray/dp/813845 |archivedate=2013-07-08 |df=}}</ref>

The third season features two commentary tracks, a gag reel, behind the scenes videos, and two features exclusive to the Blu-ray version. It was released on DVD and Blu-ray on September 6, 2011 in region 1,<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.amazon.com/dp/B003L77G2Y/ |title=Fringe: The Complete Third Season (2010) |publisher=Amazon.com |accessdate=2012-05-08}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.tvshowsondvd.com/news/Fringe-Season-3/15523 |title=Fringe - Street Date, Pricing, Specs and Bonus Material for 'Season 3' on DVD and Blu-ray |publisher=TVShowsOnDVD |first=David |last=Lambert |date=2011-06-15 |accessdate=2011-06-16 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110619082639/http://www.tvshowsondvd.com/news/Fringe-Season-3/15523 |archivedate=2011-06-19 |df=}}</ref> on September 26, 2011 in region 2,<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.amazon.co.uk/dp/B004N622D0 |title=Fringe - Season 3 (DVD) |publisher=Amazon.co.uk |accessdate=2011-05-22}}</ref> and on October 26, 2011 in region 4.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.ezydvd.com.au/DVD/fringe-the-complete-3rd-season-6-disc-set/dp/819714 |title=Fringe - The Complete 3rd Season (6 Disc Set) |publisher=EzyDVD |accessdate=2011-05-22 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120923134946/http://www.ezydvd.com.au/DVD/fringe-the-complete-3rd-season-6-disc-set/dp/819714 |archivedate=2012-09-23 |df=}}</ref>

The fourth season includes several special features, including "The Culture of ''Fringe''", a roundtable discussion with series writers and university professors regarding the science featured in the series; features on how the disappearance of Peter affects the timeline, and the role of the Observers; two features covering the ''Fringe'' comic series; and a gag reel.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.blu-ray.com/movies/Fringe-The-Complete-Fourth-Season-Blu-ray/29851/#Review |title=Fringe: The Complete Fourth Season Blu-Ray |publisher=Blu-ray.com |first=Kenneth |last=Brown |accessdate=2012-10-17 |date=2012-09-04}}</ref> It was released on DVD and Blu-ray on September 4, 2011 in region 1,<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.amazon.com/dp/B0053O8A50/ |title=Fringe: The Complete Fourth Season (2011) |accessdate=2012-10-17 |publisher=Amazon.com}}</ref> on September 24, 2012 in region 2,<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.amazon.co.uk/dp/B00538VYCW/ |title=Fringe: The Complete Fourth Season (2011) |accessdate=2012-10-17 |publisher=Amazon.co.uk}}</ref> and on October 31, 2012 in region 4.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.ezydvd.com.au/DVD/fringe-the-complete-4th-season-includes-tv-sampler/dp/6111479 |title=Fringe: The Complete 4th Season |accessdate=2012-10-17 |publisher=EzyDVD |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120916205555/http://www.ezydvd.com.au/DVD/fringe-the-complete-4th-season-includes-tv-sampler/dp/6111479 |archivedate=2012-09-16 |df=}}</ref>

The fifth season includes featurettes titled "A Farewell to ''Fringe''" and "''Fringe'' Panel at Comic-Con 2012", as well audio commentaries and a gag reel. It was released on Blu-ray and DVD on May 7, 2013 in region 1<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.tvshowsondvd.com/news/Fringe-Season-5/17990 |title=Fringe - Spring Date, Pricing, Extras and Early Art for 'The Complete 5th and Final Season' |publisher=TVShowsOnDVD |first=David |last=Lambert |date=2013-01-23 |accessdate=2013-01-23 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130125053609/http://www.tvshowsondvd.com/news/Fringe-Season-5/17990 |archivedate=2013-01-25 |df=}}</ref> and on May 13, 2013 in region 2.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.amazon.co.uk/dp/B008HE9P3E/ |title=Fringe - Season 5 |publisher=Amazon.co.uk |accessdate=2012-12-25}}</ref> A complete series box set was also released on the same dates of the fifth season release in the respective regions.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.tvshowsondvd.com/news/Fringe-The-Complete-Series/18045 |title=Fringe - Package Images Arrive for 'The Complete Series' on DVD and Blu-ray Disc |publisher=TVShowsOnDVD |first=David |last=Lambert |date=2013-02-07 |accessdate=2013-02-07 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130210031241/http://www.tvshowsondvd.com/news/Fringe-The-Complete-Series/18045 |archivedate=2013-02-10 |df=}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.amazon.co.uk/dp/B008HE9PUC/ |title=Fringe - The Complete Season 1-5 |publisher=Amazon.co.uk |accessdate=2013-02-07}}</ref>

== Other media ==
=== Games ===
An [[alternate reality game]], centered on the fictional Massive Dynamic corporation, was introduced during the pilot and featured "strange symbols paired with glowing dots" appearing throughout the episode and an "advertisement" for the company shown at the end with a web address for the game.<ref>{{cite web |title=Fringe's ARG Upsets Nature, Messes With Your Mind |url=http://io9.com/5046329/fringes-arg-upsets-nature-messes-with-your-mind |publisher=i09 |first=Meredith |last=Woerner |date=2008-09-07 |accessdate=2012-05-03}}</ref>

=== Books and comics ===
On August 27, 2008, a [[prequel]] [[comic book]] (leading right up to the moment in the pilot where Olivia 'first' meets Walter) written by [[Zack Whedon]] was released by [[DC Comics]] under its [[WildStorm]] imprint.<ref name="USA today coming attractions">{{cite web |first=Edna |last=Gundersen |author2=David Colton |url=https://www.usatoday.com/life/2008-06-12-coming-attractions_N.htm |title=Coming Attractions: The Radiators, Natalie Cole, Jeremy DeCoursey, J.J. Abrams |work=[[USA Today]] |date=2008-06-13 |accessdate=2008-09-16}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://splashpage.mtv.com/2008/08/29/dr-horrible-sings-again-gets-moist/ |title=Doctor Horrible Sings Again, Gets Moist |work=[[MTV News]] |first=Jennifer |last=Vineyard |date=2008-08-29 |accessdate=2008-09-16}}</ref> This was to be the first issue of a monthly 6-issue [[Limited series (comics)|limited series]] but the others were delayed until January 2009, when monthly publication resumed, with the sixth and final issue scheduled for release on June 17.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.comicbookresources.com/?page=article&id=20527 |title=DC Comics Solicitations for June, 2009 |publisher=Comic Book Resources |date=2009-03-23 |accessdate=2011-05-22}}</ref> The Vice President of WildStorm, [[Hank Kanalz]], explained the publication hiatus: "The writers of the show want to make sure the comic book is integrated into the mythology of the ''Fringe'' world, so we have decided to refocus the direction of the comic book. Unfortunately, this means that we will have some delays, but will be back in January."<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.newsarama.com/comics/100810-Fringe-Delay.html |title=DC's 'Fringe' Comic Delayed Until January |publisher=[[Newsarama]] |last=Brady |first=Matt |date=2008-10-10 |accessdate=2011-05-22}}</ref>

On June 23, 2010, the first issue of ''Tales From the Fringe'', the second six-part monthly series, was released, while the final issue was released on November 24, 2010.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://comics.ign.com/objects/070/070240_list.html |title=Fringe: Tales from the Fringe Comic Books |publisher=IGN |accessdate=2011-05-22}}</ref>

Additionally, in September 2011, DC released the first issue of ''Beyond the Fringe'' comic series. With the first story written by Joshua Jackson titled "Peter and the Machine". The comic issues will alternate with an 'A' story and a 'B' story each. For example, "Peter and the Machine" will take place in issues one, three, and so on until the story is finished and a new 'A' story starts up.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://insidetv.ew.com/2011/09/21/fringe-digital-comic-first-look/ |title='Fringe': Joshua Jackson pens key mythology tale in new digital comic 'Beyond the Fringe' -- FIRST LOOK |work=Entertainment Weekly |first=Jeff |last=Jensen |date=2011-09-11 |accessdate=2012-06-07}}</ref>

An encyclopedia guide, ''September's Notebook — The Bishop Paradox'', written by Tara Bennett and Paul Terry who had previously written the ''Lost Encyclopedia'' for ''[[Lost (TV series)|Lost]]'', was released in March 2013.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.tvguide.com/News/Fringe-Septembers-Notebook-1058715.aspx |title=Fringe First Look: September's Notebook |first=Dale |last=Holbrook |date=2013-01-11 |accessdate=2013-01-13 |work=[[TV Guide]]}}</ref> A three-part series of prequel novels written by [[Christa Faust]] was released throughout 2013 and 2014. Each novel deals with a member of the Fringe team's past. The first is titled ''The Zodiac Paradox'' and is about Walter and his discovery of Cortexiphan. The second in the series is titled ''The Burning Man'' and is based on Olivia and how she was first exposed to Cortexiphan. The third is titled ''Sins of the Father'' and is about Peter's life in 2008 just before the point of time when the series starts.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.fringebloggers.com/fringe-prequel-novels-the-zodiac-paradox-the-burning-man-details-pre-ordering/ |title=FRINGE Prequel Novels: The Zodiac Paradox, The Burning Man — Details & Pre-Ordering |date=2013-01-22 |accessdate=2013-04-28 |publisher=Fringe Bloggers}}</ref>

===Possible film===
At [[San Diego Comic-Con International|San Diego Comic-Con]] 2012, actor [[John Noble]] mentioned that a film could be made further down the line.<ref>{{cite web |first=Brian |last=Gallagher |title=COMIC-CON 2012: Fringe Movie May Happen Says John Noble! |url=http://www.movieweb.com/comic-con/2012/news/comic-con-2012-fringe-movie-may-happen-says-john-noble |date=July 15, 2012 |publisher=MovieWeb |accessdate=October 14, 2012}}</ref>

