'''''Ilyobacter delafieldii''''' is a [[motile]], [[gram-negative]], obligately [[Anaerobic organism|anaerobic]] rod-shaped [[bacteria]], with type strain 10cr1 (=DSM 5704). It is notable for metabolising [[beta-Hydroxybutyric acid]].<ref name="JanssenHarfoot1990">{{cite journal|last1=Janssen|first1=Peter H.|last2=Harfoot|first2=C. G.|title=Ilyobacter delafieldii sp. nov., a metabolically restricted anaerobic bacterium fermenting PHB|journal=Archives of Microbiology|volume=154|issue=3|year=1990|pages=253–259|issn=0302-8933|doi=10.1007/BF00248964}}</ref>

